result.execSummary:
The defendant Jamie R Winkler was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
Sentenced to 185 days in the Pepin County Jail.  Under the IDIP Program, defendant to serve 90 days jail with good time, with 95 days stayed upon entrance into and successful completion of the IDIP program.  Jail sentence to commence immediately.  After serving the first 48 hours without release, work release privileges granted.  Credit given for 1 day served.
AMENDED 10-13-2016:  Stay lifted, defendant to serve full 185 days.
Concurrent with: 15CT23

Operating privileges revoked for 36 months.  Under the IDIP program, operating privileges revoked for 24 months with 12 months stayed.  Credit for any administrative suspension.
AMENDED 10-13-2016:  Stay lifted, revocation for 36 months.
Submit to and comply with an alcohol assessment by the approved public treatment facility and comply with the development of a driver safety plan.

Provide a DNA sample.
Court finds defendant eligible for the IDIP Program.  Failure to comply with the program will result in all stays of the sentence to be lifted.
AMENDED 10-13-2016:  Defendant does not wish to enter into the IDIP program.  All stays lifted.
